<F P=106> [From the "24 Hours" newscast] </F>
  [Text] The main offices of two new institutions were 
announced today within the framework of NAFTA. The headquarters 
of the North American Development Bank will be located in San 
Antonio, Texas, and the Environmental Cooperation Border 
Commission will be headquartered in Ciudad Juarez, Chihuahua 
State. 
  During the first two months of this year, foreign investment 
in Mexico rose to more than $4 billion, which is 143 percent 
higher than the figure registered during the same period in 
1993, the Commerce and Industrial Development Secretariat 
announced. 

